properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 5 at 2:55PM MST until January 7 at 5:00AM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...High winds possible for Monday afternoon through Monday
night...

* WHAT...Southwest winds 35 to 50 mph with gusts up to 60 mph
possible. Gusts of 65 to 70 mph possible around Clark.

* WHERE...Cody Foothills, primarily in the vicinity of Clark

* WHEN...From Monday afternoon through late Monday night.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be difficult, especially for high
profile vehicles.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Dangerous cross winds will be possible,
especially along Highway 120 near Clark.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM MONDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH LATE MONDAY NIGHT
